Female genitalia (

Figs. 
7–10

) symmetrical. Anal tube (
Figs. 7, 9
) short, apical margin concave in ventral view. Gonopophyses VIII (first valvulae) (

Fig. 
10

) with two triangular lobes, outer lobes saw-like, strongly sclerotised with several blunt teeth on dorsal margin, inner lobes slightly sclerotised, smoothly on dorsal margin. Gonopophyses IX (second valvulae) (

Fig. 
8

) long triangular, fused together on inner-lateral margin and sclerotised, apical ends membranous and not confluent. Gonoplacs (third valvulae) (
Figs. 7, 9
) triangular with many teeth extending along ventral margin, directed mesad. Genital opening singular (monotrysian) occurring between gonopophyses VIII.
